{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"078858c5-1a67-448c-a465-abe3321d3b9d","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.mtp` package (the Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner for xUnit):\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Optionally add** to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n   This enables compatibility with `dotnet test` via the new platform (without it, use `dotnet run` or `dotnet test --enable-microsoft-testing-platform`).\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or directly:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet run -- --help   # to see MTP options\n   ```\n\nThat's the core migration. The `xunit.runner.mtp` package (available from xUnit v2.9.x+) bridges xUnit.net to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, replacing the VSTest adapter.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4bb84c25-10f7-4e82-a0c5-74f35c21ba92","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":353,"requestId":"BD0F:2586A7:1D5B15D:210899C:6A07C48F"},"id":"3b784ef8-40df-4213-b2bc-036899c413a2","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:12:55.599Z","parentId":"ae59f3d0-0938-4344-a8f4-10e0ff54a406"}
